26/12/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The EU police mission Proxima said Thursday (23 December) that Macedonia had made significant progress in police reforms, but cautioned that much remained to be done. 
A Proxima spokesman said the mission was ready to help authorities improve the quality of police work, reform the border police and boost the fight against organised crime.
In other news, an armed rebel group opened fire at a police unit in Tetovo late Friday. 
One of the attackers was killed, while a policeman and another person were injured. 
According to the Macedonian Interior Ministry, the group was led by a Kosovo paramilitary commander, Lirim Jakupi. 
UNMIK forces arrested him on Saturday in Kosovo. 
(MIA, SRNA - 25/12/04; MIA - 23/12/04)
